author: The Capital-Journal
title: Local briefs for Oct. 19, 2015: Undefeated KU volleyball moves up to No. 7 in AVCA poll
text:
By The Capital-Journal 
The Kansas volleyball team jumped up two spots to No. 7 in the American Volleyball Coaches Association (AVCA) Division I poll released Monday, marking a new program high in the coachesâ€™ rankings. 
The Jayhawks (18-0, 6-0 Big 12) downed Baylor last week to remain one of two undefeated teams in NCAA Division I, joining No. 1 Southern Cal. KU hosts Oklahoma at 6:30 p.m. Wednesday at Horejsi Family Athletic Center. 
WU VOLLEYBALL CLIMBS TO NO. 14 IN AVCA POLL: The Washburn volleyball team continued its climb up the AVCA Division II poll released Monday, jumping one spot to No. 14. 
The Ichabods (20-2, 8-2 MIAA) defeated Northwest Missouri and Missouri Western last week to move into second in the MIAA rankings. WU has been ranked in 155 consecutive AVCA polls dating back to 2003. 
WU SOCCER NOTCHES SHUTOUT: The Washburn soccer team eked out a 1-0 victory Monday at Missouri Southern, blanking the Lions to earn their fourth victory. 
The Ichabods (4-7-3, 3-3-1 MIAA) got a goal from Paige Swanson at the 51st minute, and Kaitlin Minnich notched her fourth shutout of the season for WU.
